VAs a geneticist and cell biologist I study the molecular mechanisms of chromosome segregation during mitosis and meiosis and the consequences of their failure on cell physiology. We use the budding yeast S. cerevisiae to study the final stages of mitosis and showed that this cell cycle transition is controlled by the protein phosphatase Cdc14. Our studies on the regulation of Cdc14 activity have served as a paradigm for how the activity of a protein is regulated by its changes in subcellular localization. In our work on the meiotic divisions, we investigate how regulators of the mitotic cell cycle are employed during meiosis to bring about the specialized meiotic cell cycle program.As a geneticist and cell biologist I study the molecular mechanisms of chromosome segregation during mitosis and meiosis and the consequences of their failure on cell physiology. We use the budding yeast S. cerevisiae to study the final stages of mitosis and showed that this cell cycle transition is controlled by the protein phosphatase Cdc14. Our studies on the regulation of Cdc14 activity have served as a paradigm for how the activity of a protein is regulated by its changes in subcellular localization. In our work on the meiotic divisions, we investigate how regulators of the mitotic cell cycle are employed during meiosis to bring about the specialized meiotic cell cycle program.As a geneticist and cell biologist I study the molecular mechanisms of chromosome segregation during mitosis and meiosis and the consequences of their failure on cell physiology. We use the budding yeast S. cerevisiae to study the final stages of mitosis and showed that this cell cycle transition is controlled by the protein phosphatase Cdc14. Our studies on the regulation of Cdc14 activity have served as a paradigm for how the activity of a protein is regulated by its changes in subcellular localization. In our work on the meiotic divisions, we investigate how regulators of the mitotic cell cycle are employed