VMy lab studies RNAs that regulate gene expression in animals, plants and yeast. We were among those to find that animals have many microRNAs, which are ~22-nt RNAs that specify gene repression by base-pairing to messages of protein-coding genes. We then found miRNAs in plants and have been developing increasingly reliable methods for identifying the regulatory targets of microRNAs in both plants and animals. Using these methods, we uncovered the widespread scope of microRNA-mediated regulation in animals, providing compelling evidence that most human genes are regulated by microRNAs. Our genome-wide approaches are also showing that miRNAs primarily act to decrease target mRNA levels, and experiments following-up on individual targeting interactions are revealing biological functions of microRNA action, such as how microRNAs play critical roles in plant development and how the interaction between a human microRNA and one of its regulatory targets helps prevent human cancers.My lab studies RNAs that regulate gene expression in animals, plants and yeast. We were among those to find that animals have many microRNAs, which are ~22-nt RNAs that specify gene repression by base-pairing to messages of protein-coding genes. We then found miRNAs in plants and have been developing increasingly reliable methods for identifying the regulatory targets of microRNAs in both plants and animals. Using these methods, we uncovered the widespread scope of microRNA-mediated regulation in animals, providing compelling evidence that most human genes are regulated by microRNAs. Our genome-wide approaches are also showing that miRNAs primarily act to decrease target mRNA levels, and experiments following-up on individual targeting interactions are revealing biological functions of microRNA action, such as how microRNAs play critical roles in plant development and how the interaction between a human microRNA and one of its regulatory targets helps prevent human cancers.My lab studies RNAs tha