VFarquhar develops and applies models of leaf functioning. These include the biochemical and biophysical limitations of photosynthesis, the gas exchange of water vapour and carbon dioxide through stomatal pores, carbon isotope discrimination in C3 and C4 species, and genetic variation in water-use efficiency, as well as isotope enrichment in oxygen and hydrogen of leaf water and organic matter. His linking of variation in carbon isotope composition and transpiration efficiency has provided a new tool for breeders and led to the development of wheat varieties for dry areas. His equations are also widely applied in earth systems science. His recent interests extend to large-scale issues of global change, including evaporative demand, precipitation and run-off, and effects on plants of increasing levels of carbon dioxide. Farquhar is also interested in how crop yields can be increased.Farquhar develops and applies models of leaf functioning. These include the biochemical and biophysical limitations of photosynthesis, the gas exchange of water vapour and carbon dioxide through stomatal pores, carbon isotope discrimination in C3 and C4 species, and genetic variation in water-use efficiency, as well as isotope enrichment in oxygen and hydrogen of leaf water and organic matter. His linking of variation in carbon isotope composition and transpiration efficiency has provided a new tool for breeders and led to the development of wheat varieties for dry areas. His equations are also widely applied in earth systems science. His recent interests extend to large-scale issues of global change, including evaporative demand, precipitation and run-off, and effects on plants of increasing levels of carbon dioxide. Farquhar is also interested in how crop yields can be increased.Farquhar develops and applies models of leaf functioning. These include the biochemical and biophysical limitations of photosynthesis, the gas exchange of water vapour and carbon dioxide through stomatal pores, 