VJános Kornai has become well-known as a researcher of the socialist system and post-socialist transition. He was born in Hungary and completed his studies there. He received his \u201ccandidate of science\u201d degree (an approximate equivalent of the PhD) from the Hungarian Academy of Sciences in 1956 for his Overcentralization of Economic Administration. It was published in Hungarian and later in English, the translation being based on a manuscript smuggled out of Hungary. This was the first book where an economist east of the Iron Curtain critically analyzed the foundations of the socialist system. His most well-known, the Economics of Shortage, describes the dysfunctional characteristics of the socialist system, pointing out that the chronic shortage of goods and services cannot be eliminated through reforms. His book The Socialist System provides a general overview of the communist system. In his later works he has focused on the transition between the socialist to the capitalist system. János Kornai has been president of the Econometric Society, the European Economic Association and the International Economic Association. He is a member of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences and is an associate or foreign member of the National Academy of Sciences and several other academies worldwide.János Kornai has become well-known as a researcher of the socialist system and post-socialist transition. He was born in Hungary and completed his studies there. He received his \u201ccandidate of science\u201d degree (an approximate equivalent of the PhD) from the Hungarian Academy of Sciences in 1956 for his Overcentralization of Economic Administration. It was published in Hungarian and later in English, the translation being based on a manuscript smuggled out of Hungary. This was the first book where an economist east of the Iron Curtain critically analyzed the foundations of the socialist system. His most well-known, the Economics of Shortage, describes the dysfunctional char