VAt present Alexei Starobinsky is mainly interested in the investigation of physical properties of primordial dark energy which triggered a quasi-de Sitter (inflationary) stage in the early Universe, including details of its decay resulting in the transition from this stage to the hot Big Bang, as well as of properties of present dark energy which energy density dominates the Universe now, using numerous existing and expected observational data. These two \u2018dark\u2019 entities have remarkably similar qualitative properties, and may have either physical or geometrical nature, or both. He also works in the area of classical and quantum modified gravity and its applications to cosmology, black holes, singularities and global structure of curved space-time. Among more distant, but no less fundamental and ambitious aims is the search for observational tests of the history of our Universe at the beginning of inflation and before it (including a possible bounce), as well as tests of other post-inflationary universes (\u2018multiverse\u2019) which are outside our past light cone in the approximation of a quasi-classical space-time.At present Alexei Starobinsky is mainly interested in the investigation of physical properties of primordial dark energy which triggered a quasi-de Sitter (inflationary) stage in the early Universe, including details of its decay resulting in the transition from this stage to the hot Big Bang, as well as of properties of present dark energy which energy density dominates the Universe now, using numerous existing and expected observational data. These two \u2018dark\u2019 entities have remarkably similar qualitative properties, and may have either physical or geometrical nature, or both. He also works in the area of classical and quantum modified gravity and its applications to cosmology, black holes, singularities and global structure of curved space-time. Among more distant, but no less fundamental and ambitious aims is the search for observa